defaultSir Michael Wilshawdefault: We have identified about a third of regulatory inspectors that we did not think were good enough, and we are doing something about that.  As I say, we have created a middle tier of managing inspectors in the regulatory workforce to ensure that there is good training and that performance management is robustly done and that they do a good job in the institutions that they inspect, particularly children’s homes.
